 Let x be the number of hours it takes hoses A, B, and C working together to fill the pool. According to the given information, hoses A and B together fill 1/4 of the pool in one hour, hoses A and C together fill 1/5 of the pool in one hour, and hoses B and C together fill 1/6 of the pool in one hour. Therefore, {{1/4+1/5+1/6}} = {{1/x}}. Solving for x, we get x = {{90/47}}. The answer is {{90/47}} or approximately {{90/47}} hours.</think> {{answer}}

# Challenge: A swimming pool can be filled by any of three hoses A, B or C. Hoses A and B together take 4.3 hours to fill the pool. Hoses A and C together take 5.2 hours to fill the pool. Hoses B and C together take 6.7 hours to fill the pool. How many hours does it take hoses A, B and C working together to fill the pool? Express your answer as a decimal to the nearest hundredth.


