So now, how many triangles have diagonals? Look at the lines $x+y=m$ for all $m\in(1,2,3,4,5,6)$ and it is the total number of triangles less the total number of triangles >= 20. It is a simple matter $5 \cdot 6 = 30$ excluding lines which there are $20$ of them. Therefore, $50 - 20 = 30$.
